## RFM classification — brief description

Each miRNA–target pair is classified into one of three regulatory zones based on the residual from a linear regression of cleavage confidence score (CS = 4 − DegradomeCategory) against log₂(RPKM + 1):

| Zone | Residual | Interpretation |
|---|---|---|
| **PTD** — Post-transcriptional Dominance | > +1 SD | High cleavage, low transcript: sRNA-mediated silencing dominant |
| **CR** — Compensatory Regulation | −1 SD to +1 SD | Proportional: buffered/homeostatic state |
| **TD** — Transcriptional Dominance | < −1 SD | Low cleavage, high transcript: transcriptional control dominant |

For *E. curvula* (Script 04), miRNA abundance from sRNA-seq replaces the cleavage signal, and tertile thresholds replace the SD-based cutoffs. All assignments from Script 04 are **predicted RFM states** and do not confirm cleavage activity.

